A fire broke out at a martial arts training center in China's Henan province, killing at least 18 people and leaving 16 injured, local authorities said Friday. News outlet CGTN reported that the cause of the fire in Shangqiu City is still unclear. The blaze has been fully extinguished. Police have taken the owner of the center in into custody. Local authorities are conducting an investigation into what caused the fire. more to follow... wd/rt (Reuters, AP) 